    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-28T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-28T10:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60131/63: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Estonia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leonard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tallinn</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-28T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 28, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 30—6:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. With reference to the Department’s telegram No. 4, April 26, 6 p.m. relative
                    to the extension of the Treaty of Commerce. Note <pb facs="0280" n="269"
                        xml:id="pg_269"/> suggested by the Department delivered today and will be
                    given consideration by the Foreign Office after Mr. Wirgo returns shortly from
                    Finland.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leonard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
